In a Magic the Gathering "small" set, which typically contains around 100-140 new cards, the number of cards of each type will vary depending on the specific theme and mechanics of the set. Here is a rough estimate of the number of cards of each type that might be found in a "small" set:

* Creatures: 30-50
* Instants: 10-20
* Sorceries: 10-20
* Enchantments: 10-20
* Artifacts: 10-20
* Planeswalkers: 5-10
* Lands: 10-20

It's worth noting that these are just rough estimates, and the actual number of cards of each type in a set can vary widely. The proportions of the different card types may also vary depending on the specific themes and mechanics of the set.

I hope this information helps to give you an idea of the number of cards of each type that might be found in a Magic the Gathering "small" set. Please let me know if you have any further questions.
